X: 1773445417
T: The Humours of Tulla
C: Trad.
R: reel
S: Adapted from versions at https://thesession.org/tunes/141
N: A fun tune I was shown in Durham!  First comes the basic melody, then my variations.
N: The G and Em chords are fairly interchangeable.  I mix and match them in this arrangement.
N: The ~ signs mark Irish rolls, meaning you need to do something like bow triplets to make it
N: more interesting.  Or fiddle through it, like I have in the second half of the B-part.
Z: Cam Cross 
M: 4/4
K: Dmaj
%
[P:A-part]
"D" d2Ad BdAB | "D" ~d2fd "Em" edBA | "D" d2Ad BdAd | "G" Bdef "A7" g2fe |
"D" dBAd BdAB | "D" defd "Em" edBc | "D" d2Ad BdAd | "G" (3Bcd ef "A7" gefg ||
%
[P:B-part]
"D" af ~f2 df ~f2 | "D" af ~f2 "G" g2fg | "D" af ~f2 dfed | "G" (3Bcd ef "A7" g2fg |
"D" afdf bfdf | "D" afdf "G" geBA | "D" afdf edBc | "G" defa "A7" [dg]2fe :|
%
