X: 1760203499
T: The Twenty-Eighth of January
C: Trad.
R: reel
M: 4/4
S: _KY Contra Tunes_ and thesession.org/tunes/15717 for the base
Z: Cam Cross
N: Now this is an interesting number! The B-part follows a pretty standard I/VIIb
N: progression found in many Celtic tunes, but the A-part uses the "Dorian vamp,"
N: pretty unusual in fiddle tunes but a staple in classic rock. For that reason, I
N: think it's perhaps a more "jammy" tune than a melodic one; and one version I
N: looked at had a G-F-Em-Am windup that gave it a little more of a bluesy punch.
N: The top 4 bars are the tune in its base form, and the bottom 4 bars illustrate
N: how I imagine the tune in a jam setting.
K: Ador
%
[P:A-part]
"Am" A,A,CC "D" DDFF | "Am" A,A,CC "D" D2F2 | "Am" ABcB "G" AGFG | "F" ABcB "Em" AGED |
